{"article_id":"bdDgY7QxhuvdVQdt","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"With just over a week until the first 2016 election contest , Donald Trump takes the lead in Iowa","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"-- and maintains his big advantage in New Hampshire .","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"That ' s according to the latest round of state polls on the Republican presidential nomination contest .","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"Trump bests Ted Cruz in Iowa","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"and now receives 34 percent support among Republican caucus-goers .","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"Trump was at 23 percent in the Poll two weeks ago","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"( January 4-7 ) .","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"Cruz is second with 23 percent","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"-- down a touch from 27 percent .","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"Marco Rubio comes in third with 12 percent , down from 15 percent .","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"No others garner double-digit support .","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"Among caucus-goers","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"who identify as \" very \" conservative ,","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"Cruz was up by 18 points over Trump earlier this month .","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"Now they each receive about a third among this group","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"( Cruz 34 percent vs. Trump 33 percent ) .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"There ' s been a similar shift among white evangelical Christians .","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"Cruz ' s 14-point advantage is now down to a 2-point edge .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"A lot has happened in the intervening two weeks .","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"Fox Business Network hosted a Republican debate","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"where Trump questioned Cruz ' s eligibility","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"to be president ,","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"and Cruz attacked Trump ' s liberal \" New York values. \"","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"On Tuesday , Gov . Terry Branstad urged his fellow Iowans to vote against Cruz","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"because of his opposition to ethanol","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"-- and former Vice-Presidential candidate Sarah Palin endorsed Trump .","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"Republican pollster Daron Shaw says ,","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"\" We tend to over-interpret every little thing in a presidential race ,","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"but here we actually have solid evidence","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"Trump did n't just win last week in Iowa","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"-- he won it by enough","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"to put some distance between himself and Cruz. \"","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"Shaw conducts the Poll with Democratic pollster Chris Anderson .","depth":5},{"id":33,"text":"But a lot can change before Iowans caucus February 1 .","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"A third of Republican caucus-goers say","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"they may change their mind","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"( 33 percent ) .","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"Even one in four Trump supporters says","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"they may ultimately go with another candidate","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"( 25 percent ) .","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"Cruz tops the list","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"when GOP caucus-goers are asked their second-choice candidate .","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"When first and second-choice preferences are combined ,","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"it ' s extremely tight between Trump","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"( 48 percent )","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"and Cruz","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"( 45 percent ) .","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"That ' s because 20 percent of Iowa Republican caucus-goers are so negative on Trump","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"they say","depth":13},{"id":49,"text":"they would \" refuse \" to vote for him over the Democrat in November ,","depth":13},{"id":50,"text":"while fewer say the same of Cruz","depth":13},{"id":51,"text":"( 11 percent ) .","depth":13},{"id":52,"text":"Another 14 percent say","depth":12},{"id":53,"text":"they would stay home","depth":13},{"id":54,"text":"if the nominee is Jeb Bush .","depth":13},{"id":55,"text":"Here ' s how the rest of the field stands :","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"Ben Carson is at 7 percent ,","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"Rand Paul is at 6 percent ,","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"Bush and Chris Christie each get 4 percent ,","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"Mike Huckabee , John Kasich and Rick Santorum tie at 2 percent ,","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"and Carly Fiorina gets 1 percent .","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"More than a third","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"who say","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"they will attend a Republican caucus this year","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"have never gone before","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"( 38 percent ) .","depth":9},{"id":66,"text":"Many of these first-time attendees , 43 percent , are supporting Trump ,","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"while 19 percent favor Cruz","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"and 14 percent Rubio .","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"The poll can ' t predict","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"how many from this group will actually show up .","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"Among just those Republicans","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"who have caucused before ,","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"it ' s a 3-point race :","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"Trump 28 percent vs. Cruz 25 percent .","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"Another 10 percent go for Rubio .","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"True conservative values is the top characteristic","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"GOP caucus-goers want in their party ' s nominee","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"( 27 percent ) ,","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"closely followed by telling it like it is","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"( 24 percent )","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"and being a strong leader","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"( 23 percent ) .","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"Those traits outrank nominating someone","depth":6},{"id":84,"text":"who can win in November","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"( 9 percent )","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"or has the right experience","depth":8},{"id":87,"text":"( 7 percent ) .","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"Unlike Iowa , there has been little movement in the New Hampshire Republican race .","depth":5},{"id":89,"text":"Trump continues to garner more than twice the support of his nearest competitors .","depth":6},{"id":90,"text":"The poll shows Trump at 31 percent","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"( down 2 points ) ,","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"Cruz at 14 percent","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"( up 2 points )","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"and Rubio at 13 percent","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"( down 2 points ) .","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"Kasich is at 9 percent ,","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"Bush and Christie each receive 7 percent ,","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"Carson and Paul tie at 5 percent ,","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"while Fiorina gets 3 percent ,","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"and Huckabee 1 percent .","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"Despite dominating the NH race ,","depth":7},{"id":102,"text":"Trump also tops the list as the nominee","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"who would make Republicans stay home in November :","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"26 percent say","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"they would refuse to vote for Trump against the Democrat .","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"Fifteen percent say the same of Bush ,","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"14 percent feel that way about Cruz ,","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"and 12 percent about Rubio .","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"Over half of likely Republican primary voters in the Granite State say","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"they are certain to vote for their candidate ,","depth":8},{"id":111,"text":"while 36 percent could still shift their support .","depth":7},{"id":112,"text":"Granite Staters also want slightly different traits in their nominee than their Iowa counterparts .","depth":6},{"id":113,"text":"NH GOP primary voters want a strong leader","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"( 27 percent )","depth":8},{"id":115,"text":"and someone","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"who tells it like it is","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"( 21 percent )","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"more than a nominee","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"who has true conservative values","depth":11},{"id":120,"text":"( 15 percent ) ,","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"is electable","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"( 13 percent ) ,","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"or has the right experience","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"( 12 percent ) .","depth":12},{"id":125,"text":"The Poll is conducted under the joint direction of Anderson Robbins Research","depth":4},{"id":126,"text":"( D )","depth":4},{"id":127,"text":"and Shaw & Company Research","depth":4},{"id":128,"text":"( R ) .","depth":4},{"id":129,"text":"These polls were conducted January 18-21 , 2016 , by telephone","depth":5},{"id":130,"text":"( landline and cellphone )","depth":5},{"id":131,"text":"with live interviewers .","depth":4},{"id":132,"text":"The New Hampshire poll was among a sample of 801 registered voters","depth":6},{"id":133,"text":"selected from a statewide voter file .","depth":6},{"id":134,"text":"Results","depth":7},{"id":135,"text":"based on the sample of 401 Republican primary voters","depth":7},{"id":136,"text":"have a margin of sampling error of plus or minus five percentage points .","depth":6},{"id":137,"text":"In Iowa , the poll was among a sample of 801 registered voters","depth":6},{"id":138,"text":"selected from a statewide voter file .","depth":6},{"id":139,"text":"Results","depth":7},{"id":140,"text":"based on the sample of 378 Republican caucus-goers","depth":7},{"id":141,"text":"have a margin of sampling error of plus or minus five percentage points .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":283,"left":266,"right":282,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":266,"left":174,"right":265,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":174,"left":144,"right":173,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":144,"left":143,"right":2,"